message: The 'stove' is your best friend! Use it on all raw ingredients. Cooked proteins and most cooked vegetables will become valuable (20 points each). Cooked grains, however, might still be worth 0. To achieve a 40-point item, you have two reliable options: 1) Combine a 'cooked protein' with a 'cooked grain'. 2) Combine two 'cooked vegetables' together. Crucially, DO NOT overcomplicate! Hello future crafter! The previous player's advice about 'water being useless' and 'not overcomplicating' is critical. Your best strategy is to:
1. Use the 'ğŸ”¥ stove' to cook a 'raw protein' (like egg, beef, fish, bacon, or beans). This will make an item worth 20 points.
2. Combine this 'cooked protein' with *one* 'grain' (like bread, wheat, corn, or rice) OR *one* 'vegetable' (like cucumber, potato, or carrot). This will create an item worth 40 points.
Do NOT combine items that are already worth 40 points, as this consistently leads to 'overcomplicated' items with negative values. Also, remember that ingredients are consumed when used. Aim for a single 40-point item and then submit.
